definition.value: A member of the class of cinnamates that is the conjugate base of trans-sinapic acid.
A cobalt coordination entity consisting of six amino groups bound to a central cobalt atom.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the carboxy groups of succinic acid.
A diterpene consisting of taxane having two C=C double bonds at the 4(5)- and 11(12)-positions.
A taxane diterpenoid that is taxane which contains double bounds at the 4-20 and 11-12 positions and which is substituted by hydroxy groups at the 5alpha and 13alpha positions.
A taxane diterpenoid that is taxane which contains double bounds at the 4-20 and 11-12 positions and which is substituted by an acetoxy group at the 5alpha position.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy groups of terephthalic acid.

Bacterial polysaccharide derivatives of glycerol phosphate or ribitol phosphate linked via phosphodiester bonds, whose main function is to fortify the cell wall. In some parasites, they serve as a site of attachment to mucosal membranes.
A phenethylamine alkaloid that is N-methyl-4-methoxyphenylethylamine carrying an additional N-(3,4-dimethoxybenzyl) substituent.
